On this 57 min. live cd, Mary Mack talks about her family a lot, and that makes other people feel better about themselves. Also, she speaks and sings of plenty of awkward moments that help you laugh if you ever get stuck in one. Some things commonly heard at a Mary Mack show:"I hate comedy, but I liked you." (We don't know if this is good or bad...probably good. "I haven't belly laughed in a long time." (Belly laughs are good for the hormones, plus you don't need to do any sit-ups that day. "I'll have some of what she's smoking." (Mack isn't smoking anything. She's just normally weird. Rumor has it that Mack plans to have some re-editing done to this album and re-release it as an actual vinyl record. Obviously, she's not in it for the money.

Rated PG 13, not for dummies.
